KASIMBA stalked three wide, ranged up to the leader from the three path turning for home, produced a bid in midstretch along with an inner rival, got outkicked by that one passing the furlong pole, ran on well in pursuit thereafter, but was kept at bay. ALL JOKES ASIDE set the pace along the inside, shifted outwardly as an outer rival ranged up nearing the lane, held an advantage through upper stretch while hanging on his left lead, but yielded to bidders on either side at the furlong grounds. PLATINUM GHOST laid off of the pace while caught in the five path into the turn, took a light brush from an inner rival inside the three furlong pole, then sustained stride while hanging on his left lead throughout the lane, and lacked a bid. HYPER SPEED raced at the rear, dropped back to trail in the two path entering the turn, moved up by splitting foes two wide entering the lane, but flattened out without reaching contention. VALUABLE CARGO lacked speed in the four path and between horses, took light contact from an inner rival leaving the three furlong pole, transferred that brush to an outer rival in the process, then failed to menace among foes through the lane. GIANT AWAKENING chased along the inside and tired turning for home. LEVEL UP raced forward two wide and between horses into the turn, but gave way at the three furlong pole before being brushed by an inner foe, and continued to weaken.
